  <roomsDescription><![CDATA[<p><strong>Superior Twin/Double Rooms</strong> are around 25-28m² and sleep up to three people (extra bed is a single sofa bed). These rooms have an ensuite with shower and are available for sole occupancy for a supplement.</p>
<p><strong>Executive Twin/Double Rooms</strong> are around 26-30m² and sleep two to three people (extra bed is a single sofa bed). These rooms have a balcony, ensuite with shower and mountain view.</p>
<p><strong>Family Rooms </strong>sleep four people (extra bed is a double sofa bed (145 centimetres' wide) in the same sleeping area). These rooms have a balcony and ensuite with bath (with overhead shower).</p>
<p><strong>Luxurious Suites </strong>sleep two to five people with a bedroom with double bed and a living room with sofa beds - a double sofa bed (145 centimetres' wide) and single sofa bed (70 centimetres' wide). The living room is separate from the bedroom but there's no door between the two. These rooms have a balcony and two ensuites, one with bath and one with shower.</p>
<p><strong>All rooms have:</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>TV</li>
<li>Air conditioning</li>
<li>Safe</li>
<li>Minibar/fridge</li>
<li>Hairdryer</li>
<li>Bathrobes &amp; slippers</li>
</ul>
<p><strong>General information</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Check-in: <strong>2pm</strong></li>
<li>Check-out: <strong>11am</strong></li>
</ul>
<p><strong>Local fees and taxes</strong></p>
<p>A resort tourist tax of approx. €2.50 per person per night is payable locally. Children aged 7-18 years pay a discounted rate of approx. €1 per night, and children aged 6 and under are exempt.</p>
<p><strong>Accessibility</strong></p>
<ul>
<li>Adapted rooms: <strong>3</strong></li>
</ul>]]></roomsDescription>
